Alembic migrations for the Assessment Platform (single-database config).

The URL is NOT stored in alembic.ini — env.py reads it from config.DATABASE_URL,
the same env var the service uses. Pass it per-invocation:

  # apply all migrations (production schema bootstrap / upgrade)
  DATABASE_URL="postgresql+psycopg://..." uv run alembic upgrade head

  # after changing a model, autogenerate the next revision, then review it
  DATABASE_URL="sqlite:///./platform.db" uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

Dev/tests don't need this — the app calls SQLModel.metadata.create_all on
startup. The initial migration is autogenerated from that same metadata, so the
two stay at parity.
